A vast, cluttered landscape of abandoned filing cabinets, folders, and dusty document towers stretching to the horizon under an overcast sky, rendered in Studio Ghibli's signature soft watercolor style. In the foreground, a small group of people stand on separate floating islands made of office furniture, reaching toward each other across impossible gaps but unable to connect. Gentle wind carries loose papers between them like migrating birds. The mood is melancholic yet hopeful, with warm amber light breaking through clouds in the distance where the isolated islands seem to gradually merge into a single connected landmass. Overgrown vines and small plants sprout from the abandoned infrastructure, suggesting nature reclaiming failed systems. The color palette shifts from cool grays and blues in the cluttered foreground to warm golds and greens toward the unified horizon.
